<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-32-1172 </DOCNO><TEXT>The paper briefly describes the transport of coal, limestone and minerals(copper and iron) through pipelines - a modern and future oriented methodof ensuring the supply of energy and raw materials, with economical andenvironmental benefits. A survey is made of existing slurry pipelines.The factors influencing pipeline economics - land, equipment, energy,chemical treatment and maintenance costs, are discussed. The paper alsoprovides flowsheets and major equipment specifications.</TEXT></DOC>